.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_LIB\f[R]
Override the library directory.
The selected directory must contain \f[V]lib/common.sh\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_PROFILE\f[R]
Override the active OS profile for the current invocation.
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_NONINTERACTIVE\f[R]
Disable interactive prompting where supported.
Individual destructive operations may still require their dedicated
confirmation gate.
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_ASSUME_YES\f[R]
Set to \f[V]1\f[R] for commands that explicitly support non-interactive
confirmation.
It does not replace destructive-operation gates.
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_CONFIRM_DESTROY\f[R]
Must be set to \f[V]YES\f[R] where a destructive install or decommission
operation explicitly requires it.
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_LOG_LEVEL\f[R]
Logging threshold: \f[V]debug\f[R], \f[V]info\f[R], \f[V]warn\f[R], or
\f[V]error\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_METRICS_DIR\f[R]
Prometheus textfile collector directory.
.TP
\f[B]SOVEREIGN_OS_METRICS_DISABLE\f[R]
Set to \f[V]1\f[R] to suppress Layer B metric emission.
.PP
All supported variables and their consumers are discoverable through
\f[B]sovereign-osctl env list\f[R].
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]/etc/sovereign-os/active-profile\f[R]
Installed active-profile selector.
.TP
\f[B]/etc/sovereign-os/active-whitelabel\f[R]
Installed whitelabel selector.
.TP
\f[B]/usr/local/lib/sovereign-os\f[R]
Default installed library tree.
.TP
\f[B]/usr/lib/sovereign-os\f[R]
Legacy library location.
.TP
\f[B]/opt/sovereign-os\f[R]
Alternate vendor tree used by installed services.
.TP
\f[B].sovereign-os/init-state.yaml\f[R]
Setup-wizard state in a repository or operator working directory.
.TP
\f[B]/var/lib/sovereign-os/\f[R]
Per-machine runtime state.
.TP
\f[B]/mnt/vault/models/\f[R]
Model catalog on ZFS-tiered profiles.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Inspect system state in machine-readable form:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl status --json
sovereign-osctl doctor
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Inspect the effective primary profile:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl profiles show-effective sain-01
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Inspect model placement options:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl models suggest --runtime-profile high-concurrency --json
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Verify build provenance deeply:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl audit provenance --deep       build/sain-01/output/build-provenance.json
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Plan image installation without writing:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
sovereign-osctl install image --plan       build/sain-01/output/sain-01.raw --to /dev/nvme1n1
\f[R]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.PP
Zero indicates success.
Non-zero indicates invalid input, a failed check, an unavailable
dependency, a refused safety gate, or an operational failure.
Some audit and coverage commands use status 2 to report findings or
gaps.
